text.tspan: Future Directions: Amaranthus crop/weed hybrid incompatibility mapping
Amaranthus includes >70 species most of which are interfertile.
Commercially important crops (amaranth; A. hypochondriacus). and weedy
Hybrids tend to exhibit variable (incomplete) seed or pollen inviability.
Large-scale RAD-seq phylogeny and network analysis from USDA germplasm.
Successful crosses between two distantly related weed species, and weeds to crops.
Troubleshooting of pollen and seed viability measurements and automation
